				<note resp="Philip Lampi">The vote totals in District 8 are estimated, being based on the ratio of votes cast in the surrounding districts between 1796-1800.  D.H. Gilpatrick, in his book JEFFERSONIAN DEMOCRACY IN NORTH CAROLINA 1789-1816, notes that David Stone was elected, having 375 more votes than Charles Johnson and 450 more than Dempsey Burgess.  I have therefore applied Gilpatrick's figures for David Stone in District 8 to obtain returns for this election.</note>
